        "faq_item_yUrmMy": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can the weight of an adhered masonry veneer system impact the design of its structural backing?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. As with all cladding systems, adhered veneers do not contribute to the design strength of the wall assembly and instead transfer loads into their structural backing. Whether these loads are present, as well as their orientation and magnitude, will vary depending on the load under consideration (wind, seismic, gravity, etc.) and the type of cladding system being detailed (anchored masonry veneer, adhered masonry veneer, or other system). By addressing these common questions, we aim to provide clarity and confidence in choosing Creative Mines' manufactured stone veneer products for your next project.</p>",
            "faqvideo": "",
            "cat_option1": false,
            "cat_option2": false,
            "cat_option3": true,
            "cat_option4": false,
            "cat_option5": false,
            "cat_option6": false,
            "cat_option7": false,
            "cat_option8": false,
            "cat_option9": false,
            "cat_option10": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_dzmD6b": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are your products non-combustible?",
            "answer": "<p>Our lightweight concrete stone veneer is meticulously engineered with specific attention to its fire-resistant & non-combustible properties. The main components of our veneer include Portland cement, lightweight aggregates, pozzolan, mineral oxide colors, and concrete admixtures. Notably, it exhibits \"0\" flame spread and \"0\" Smoke-developed properties when tested in accordance with ASTM E84-23 Standard Method of Test for Surface Burning Characteristics of Building Materials (UL 723, ANSI/NFPA No.255, and UBC No.18-1).</p>",
            "faqvideo": "",
            "cat_option1": false,
            "cat_option2": false,
            "cat_option3": true,
            "cat_option4": false,
            "cat_option5": false,
            "cat_option6": false,
            "cat_option7": false,
            "cat_option8": false,
            "cat_option9": false,
            "cat_option10": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_bptXkB": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the R-value of your stone veneer?",
            "answer": "<p>The R-value contribution of our products to the wall will vary by profile due to the product’s thickness, the wall’s assembly, and the installation technique grouted joint vs dry-stacked. Consult the projects architect or design engineer for specific R-value.</p>",
            "faqvideo": "",
            "cat_option1": false,
            "cat_option2": false,
            "cat_option3": true,
            "cat_option4": false,
