        "faq_item_Berhaf": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does the cost of manufactured stone compare to natural stone?",
            "answer": "<p>Manufactured stone veneer often costs about half to two-thirds less than natural stone veneer because:<br/><br/><strong>Raw Materials & Production<br/></strong>Creative Mines stone and brick veneer is created using lightweight aggregates and molds, reducing the need for quarrying, cutting, and transporting heavy natural stone.<br/><br/><strong>Installation Efficiency<br/></strong>Its lighter weight means fewer structural modifications and simpler installation methods—lowering labor and equipment costs compared to natural stone veneer.<strong><br/><br/>Reduced Waste<br/></strong>Creative Mines is made to consistent shapes and sizes, minimizing cutting and leftover material, which saves both time and money.<br/><br/><strong>Predictable Supply<br/></strong>Because it’s produced in a controlled setting, Creative Mines stone and brick veneer offers more stable pricing and availability, avoiding the supply fluctuations common with natural stone. In addition, color palettes are manufactured consistently, making design and future additions more reliable than the variations found with natural stone.</p>",
            "faqvideo": "",
            "cat_option1": false,
            "cat_option2": false,
            "cat_option3": false,
