        "faq_item_UJiTa3": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are your products LEED-certified or suitable for green building projects?",
            "answer": "<p>Creative Mines can help earn LEED points in several key areas:<strong><br/><br/>Materials & Resources (MR): </strong>Recycled Content & Regional Sourcing: If your stone includes recycled materials or is produced locally, it can boost credits for reducing environmental impact through resource optimization. Life-Cycle Assessments & EPDs: Documenting a lower environmental footprint through environmental product declarations can further enhance sustainability credentials.<br/>Indoor Environmental Quality (IEQ):<strong><br/><br/>Low VOC Emissions: </strong>Manufactured stone typically has low volatile organic compounds, contributing to better indoor air quality.<br/><br/><strong>Innovation (IN): </strong>New Sustainable Practices: If your product uses breakthrough technologies or materials (like incorporating Pozzolan for reduced carbon footprint), it can secure innovation credits.<br/>Energy & Atmosphere (EA):<strong><br/><br/>Thermal Mass Benefits:</strong> While not a direct LEED credit, the durability and energy efficiency of quality manufactured stone can contribute indirectly to overall energy performance strategies.</p><p>Please refer to our <a href=\"https://d2ho1mx8zrpzgz.cloudfront.net/pdfs/LEED-points-contribution.pdf\">LEED Contribution Data Sheet </a>available on our website.</p>",
            "faqvideo": "",
