        "faq_item_hkttp3": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How is Pozzolan technology better for the environment?",
            "answer": "<p>Pozzolan not only cuts down on CO₂ emissions—it’s a game-changer for sustainable building. Here’s what makes Creative Mines stone, brick and masonry veneers shine;</p><p><strong>Waste Reduction & Circular Economy: </strong>Sourced from natural volcanic ash, Pozzolan turns what might have been waste into a valuable resource. This supports circular economy principles and minimizes landfill contributions.<br/><br/><strong>Enhanced Durability:</strong> Beyond boosting strength, Pozzolan’s lower heat of hydration reduces thermal stress during curing and reduces the chance for chemical attacks. This means fewer cracks, lower maintenance needs, and a longer-lasting product that stands up well in all elements.<br/><br/><strong>Energy Efficiency & Green Certifications:</strong> With a more efficient manufacturing process and a lower overall carbon footprint, by Creative Mines incorporating Pozzolan into its mix design it can help projects meet green building standards and certifications, adding both environmental and market value.</p>",
            "faqvideo": "",
