        "faq_itemtwo_nA8XCq": {
          "type": "faq_itemtwo",
          "settings": {
            "question_1": "Can manufactured stone be installed over existing brick, concrete, or drywall?",
            "answer_1": "<p>Manufactured stone can be installed directly to existing brick and concrete surfaces as long as it is clean, untreated, unsealed, structurally sound, and is properly prepared. For drywall surfaces, it will require prep work to make the wall suitable to receive our stone veneer. Download CMHA Installation Guidelines <a href=\"https://d2ho1mx8zrpzgz.cloudfront.net/pdfs/CMHA-MANUFACTURED-STONE-INSTALL-GUIDELINES-ENGLISH.pdf\">here</a>.</p>",
            "faqvideo_1": "",
            "cat_option1_1": false,
            "cat_option2_1": true,
            "cat_option3_1": false,
            "cat_option4_1": false,
            "cat_option5_1": false,
            "cat_option6_1": false,
            "cat_option7_1": false,
            "cat_option8_1": false,
            "cat_option9_1": false,
            "cat_option10_1": false,
            "question_2": "How do your products perform in various climate conditions?",
            "answer_2": "<p>Creative Mines masonry veneers excel in all weather conditions the seasons can produce. Our industry leading freeze-thaw durability with 0% degradation, 3800 compressive strength, and superior resistance to moisture intrusion and unsightly efflorescence is unmatched.</p>",
            "faqvideo_2": "",
            "cat_option1_2": false,
            "cat_option2_2": false,
            "cat_option3_2": false,
            "cat_option4_2": true,
            "cat_option5_2": true,
            "cat_option6_2": false,
            "cat_option7_2": false,
            "cat_option8_2": false,
            "cat_option9_2": false,
            "cat_option10_2": false,
            "question_3": "What is the fire rating of Creative Mines' products?",
            "answer_3": "<p>Our stone veneer is meticulously engineered with specific attention to its fire-resistant properties. The main components of our veneer include portland cement, lightweight aggregates, pozzolan, mineral oxide colors, and concrete admixtures. Notably, it exhibits \"0\" flame spread and \"0\" Smoke-developed properties when tested in accordance with ASTM E84-23 Standard Method of Test for Surface Burning Characteristics of Building Materials (UL 723, ANSI/NFPA No.255, and UBC No.18-1).</p>",
            "faqvideo_3": "",
            "cat_option1_3": false,
            "cat_option2_3": false,
            "cat_option3_3": false,
            "cat_option4_3": true,
            "cat_option5_3": true,
            "cat_option6_3": false,
            "cat_option7_3": false,
            "cat_option8_3": false,
            "cat_option9_3": false,
            "cat_option10_3": false,
            "question_4": "Does manufactured stone fade over time?",
            "answer_4": "<p>Creative Mines stone veneer are designed with a gladiator tough concrete mix design that incorporates the use of a pozzolan -a natural additive found in icons like the colosseum, that outperforms and outlasts all other manufactured stone veneers products. Its integral color throughout the product and surface colorations to closely mimic natural stone. They are engineered to maintain their aesthetic appeal throughout the stone veneer’s lifespan. All products are backed by a 50-Year Limited Warranty.</p>",
            "faqvideo_4": "",
            "cat_option1_4": false,
            "cat_option2_4": false,
            "cat_option3_4": false,
            "cat_option4_4": true,
            "cat_option5_4": true,
            "cat_option6_4": false,
            "cat_option7_4": false,
            "cat_option8_4": false,
            "cat_option9_4": false,
            "cat_option10_4": false,
            "question_5": "What makes Creative Mines' stone unique compared to competitors?",
            "answer_5": "<p>Creative Mines is the only stone veneer manufacturer that uses a natural pozzolan to create a gladiator tough concrete mix design. Its proprietary mix design provides high compressive strength, with unmatched freeze-thaw durability performance, and physical properties that control efflorescence in the veneer.</p>",
            "faqvideo_5": "",
            "cat_option1_5": false,
            "cat_option2_5": false,
            "cat_option3_5": false,
            "cat_option4_5": true,
            "cat_option5_5": true,
