            "cat_option7_5": false,
            "cat_option8_5": false,
            "cat_option9_5": false,
            "cat_option10_5": false,
            "question_6": "What materials are used in Creative Mines' manufactured stone?",
            "answer_6": "<p>Creative Mines uses a gladiator concrete mix design that consists of portland cement, natural pozzolan, lightweight aggregates, and iron oxide pigments to ensure each piece mirrors the physical properties and colors of natural stone.</p>",
            "faqvideo_6": "",
            "cat_option1_6": false,
            "cat_option2_6": false,
            "cat_option3_6": false,
            "cat_option4_6": true,
            "cat_option5_6": false,
            "cat_option6_6": false,
            "cat_option7_6": false,
            "cat_option8_6": false,
            "cat_option9_6": false,
            "cat_option10_6": false,
            "question_7": "What is manufactured stone, and how is it different from natural stone?",
            "answer_7": "<p>Manufactured stone veneer is designed to replicate the appearance and texture of natural stone. These products provide the aesthetic appeal of natural stone with the added benefits of reduced weight and easier installation. They typically offer a more cost-effective solution than natural stone. It eliminates the need for additional structural support, footings, or wall ties, and its lighter weight can reduce installation time and labor costs.</p>",
            "faqvideo_7": "",
            "cat_option1_7": false,
            "cat_option2_7": false,
            "cat_option3_7": false,
            "cat_option4_7": true,
            "cat_option5_7": false,
