            "cat_option8_8": false,
            "cat_option9_8": false,
            "cat_option10_8": false,
            "question_9": "Is sealing stone and brick veneer necessary?",
            "answer_9": "<p>Sealing is not required for manufactured stone and brick veneer, but it can offer added protection, particularly in areas exposed to water, dirt, or smoke. A breathable, non-film-forming masonry sealer—such as one with silane or siloxane—can help prevent stains and make cleaning easier. For large-format, light colored stone, sealing is especially beneficial during installation and over time to minimize staining.</p>",
            "faqvideo_9": "",
